What you need to know:

Former German Chancellor Angela Merkel awkwardly refused to call herself a feminist during an onstage event in 2017.But in September of last year, Merkel appeared to have a change of heart, saying she believes that “men and women are equal”.In her early years as chancellor, she supported female-friendly laws such as paid parental leave, expansion of public kindergartens, and the legal right to a kindergarten spot for children from the age of one.